b'In an effort to continue listening and learning, we want to hear from you. We\xe2\x80\x99re looking to partner with leaders in the Black community who are doing great work, and we want to use our platform to amplify their voice. Tag your favorite creators and community leaders in the comments.'

b'To our Clinique Community,
We stand in solidarity with our Black employees, Black consumers and Black communities & firmly believe Black lives matter.
We don\xe2\x80\x99t have all the answers, but we\xe2\x80\x99re committed on this journey together to listen, learn and act.\xc2\xa0
We will continue to reflect on how we can do better and work towards ending systemic racism.\xc2\xa0
We will commit to advocate for change and compassion.
We will be transparent about the work we are doing today, while we continue our ongoing journey of education, reflection & improvement.
-\xc2\xa0
These are the four areas of action.
-
Community support:
*We reached out to our community for recommendations of organizations pushing for systemic changes, including racial and social justice, and have committed donations to\xc2\xa0@urbanjusticecenter, #raceforward (raceforward.org), & @naacp.
-
Changes from within:
*Provide mandatory unconscious bias training - expand training to all full-time US Clinique employees.
*ELC to match employee donations - *available to eligible U.S. & U.K.-based employees, up to the employee\xe2\x80\x99s individual company match cap through June 2020.
-\xc2\xa0
Talent investment: *Talent acquisition - reach U.S. population parity for our Black employees for all levels in the next five years.
*Provide equitable access to professional development and advancement for our Black employees in the U.S.
*Hold ourselves accountable for creating a workforce that is more representative and responsive to people of all backgrounds.
*Organize a brand-wide Day of Solidarity that focuses on learning, action and service.
-\xc2\xa0
Representation: *Ensure end-to-end creative process accurately and consistently represents the Black experience, engages Black professionals and continue to evolve our products to better meet the needs of our Black consumers.
*We will increase our pool of Black talent among our behind-the-camera creative teams and require input from Black professionals or consumers in the development of concepts.
*Increased representation of Black talent in campaigns.
-\xc2\xa0
This is an on-going conversation and we will continue to learn and grow together.
Your Clinique Family'
